Last night at the WSL Award Ceremony ✨

So blessed to be included in such a special ceremony. Watching all the Keiki get so involved by learning the oli, making their kīhei, and making each lei to be offered to the surfers was truly inspiring. I’m especially in awe of the beautiful wahine who organized and guided each child through the entire process which I promise you is no easy task, with such grace and patience. Love you @lyndieirons @tammymoniz @momakoral @makemagicmalia you truly are treasures to the community ✨

“Music is a universal language. You don’t have to speak Hawaiian to enjoy Hawaiian music. Emotions and words are communicated through the dancer’s visual interpretation of the story, setting the intention that the more you understand, the more you can appreciate. Sharing our aloha in the form of song and dance with all the competitors starting in the WSL World Tour at the Pipe Pro”. @tiarabellaaa @keliamoniz & @nanea.alden sharing the beautiful meaning & custom of dancing hula during the opening ceremony at the Pipe contest this week ✨
Thank you for teaching us this beautiful dance @tammymoniz and for bringing us all closer together ♥️

I’ve danced hula my whole life♥️ 
My mother was a hula dancer. She met my father who was a drummer for the Al Harrington show in Waikiki. It has been so special to dance as an adult with my sisters and best friends. Teaching them what my mother taught me and Aunty Tammy teaching us what she has learned from her Kumu as well. I love seeing their love for hula grow more and more and seeing their little ones surrounded by it.  Seeing them watch they’re mothers and aunties dance together reminds me of when I was a little girl watching my mom and aunties dance and beginning my love for hula. Full circle moment. ♥️ I live for these moments!

Our Leader.. Our Sister… Our Queen @andersenlisa 👑

Tonight we celebrated @andersenlisa 30 years with @roxy. She truly is a pioneer for women’s surfing. Hearing everyone’s stories of Lisa tonight was truly inspiring. In a male dominated sport, Lisa was the first female surfer to be featured on the cover of Surfer Magazine and the only mother to win a World Title 🤯. There was a time when surf companies didn’t manufacture ANYTHING for women!!! I know crazy right!!?! Lisa was first signed to Quicksilver and wore men’s board shorts. When Roxy was developed in the 90s, Lisa designed the first boardshorts for women, trailblazing entire collections designed for women by women. Because of her, today we get so many amazing collaborations - Kelia Moniz, Steph Gilmore, and Kate Bosworth to name a few. Each so iconic and paving the way for up and coming female surfers. So the next time you go surfing and put on board shorts, a wet suit, a bikini or a one piece, remember there was someone who made that possible for you, and that person is Lisa Andersen.  Congratulations Lisa, we love you so much and I’m so honored to be your team member and friend. To 30 more years of inspiring us all. Cheee Huuuuu 🥂💕
